Yes.  That is exactly how it works.  Not only Medicare but most
insurance companies require you to go to "in-network" doctors that have
agreements with the insurance company as to how much they will pay for
every procedure.  If you go the the in-network doctor that is all you
will have to pay for no matter what the actual bill is, of you go to an
out-of-network doctor you may have to pay more out of your own pocket.

--
-Ernie-
